Tools needed for drive work, including MMC URLs:

* Precision screwdriver set (phillips and slot):
https://www.mcmaster.com/52985A21

* Tap wrench:
https://www.mcmaster.com/2546A23

* M1, #0-80, #2-56, and #4-40 taps (plug-chamfer 2-flute TiN-coated):
https://www.mcmaster.com/2504A25
https://www.mcmaster.com/2636A112
https://www.mcmaster.com/26955A11
https://www.mcmaster.com/26955A13

* Pin vise for drilling (you may need a smaller one for M1):
https://www.mcmaster.com/7112A2

* Various drill bits for tapping holes and clearance holes:
https://www.mcmaster.com/2901A108   (1/32" - M1 tap)
https://www.mcmaster.com/2901A109   (3/64" - M1 clear, #0 tap)
https://www.mcmaster.com/2901A225   (50ga - #2 tap, #0 clear)
https://www.mcmaster.com/2901A113   (3/32" - #4 tap, #2 clear)
https://www.mcmaster.com/2901A115   (1/8" - #4 clear)

* For screws, the most commonly-used ones are:
https://www.mcmaster.com/91772A054   (#0-80 3/16" pan-head phillips)
https://www.mcmaster.com/91772A055   (#0-80 1/4" pan-head phillips)
https://www.mcmaster.com/91772A079   (#2-56 3/8" pan-head phillips)
https://www.mcmaster.com/96640A025   (#2-56 3/8" flat-head phillips)


